Reasoning: The paper deals with communication channels, transmission rates, and information theory, which are all topics covered in the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The presence of an eavesdropper and the focus on secrecy also suggest the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The use of game theory concepts and the connection established between multiuser channels and observation structures in dynamic games suggest the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category. The paper also deals with achievable rate regions and transmission rates for specific types of channels, which could fall under the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the use of perturbations to increase the rate region suggests the cs.GN (General Mathematics) sub-category.
